\begin_layout Standard
The doctoral thesis written by Dalian University of Technology doctoral
 students should meet the requirements of writing standards and formatting.
 The following format is the doctoral thesis template prepared by the graduate
 school in accordance with national and industry standards, for reference
 by doctoral students.
 The abstract of a thesis is a microcosm of the thesis, and the text should
 be concise and clear.
 The content should include the purpose, method, results, and conclusion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The abstract of a thesis is a microcosm of the thesis, and the text should
 be concise and clear.
 The content should include the purpose, method, results, and conclusion.
 The unit system shall be converted to the International Standard System
 of Measurement, and except for special circumstances, all numbers shall
 be in Arabic numerals.
 Illustrations are not allowed in the text, and important tables can be
 written in.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The main content of the abstract is to briefly describe the purpose and
 significance of the entire article, the methods used, the main research
 content, and conclusions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The length is limited to one to two pages, and 3-5 keywords are listed after
 the main body of the abstract, with a blank line between the keywords and
 the abstract.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Keyword: "is a guide for the keyword section and cannot be omitted.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Please try to use the standardized words provided in the "Chinese Thesaurus"
 and other word lists for keywords.
 Use semicolons between keywords, without punctuation at the end.
\end_layout

